<h2>2. Vultr — Best Global Coverage for Low-Latency Inference</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.3/5</strong></p>
<p>Vultr stands out with <strong>32 data center regions</strong> worldwide — more than any other provider at this price point. This makes it ideal for deploying AI inference endpoints close to your users across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and Australia.</p>

<p>Vultr offers a broad GPU lineup including NVIDIA A100 (80GB), A40 (48GB), and AMD Instinct GPUs, available as both virtual machines and bare metal. Their <strong>Cloud GPU</strong> instances start at $90/month, and CPU-only <strong>Cloud Compute</strong> instances start at $2.50/month (IPv6-only) or $3.50/month (with IPv4) — making Vultr one of the cheapest options for lightweight AI API hosting.</p>

<p>For containerized AI workloads, Vultr's Kubernetes Engine supports GPU-accelerated pods, and their Serverless Inference platform simplifies model deployment at scale.</p>

